FBIS4-37494 "drnes120dd_94014" FBIS-NES-94-120 Daily Report 20 Jun 1994 Palestinian Affairs Private TV Station Said Planned for Autonomy Area Private TV Station Said Planned for Autonomy Area TA2106140494 Jerusalem AL-NAHAR in Arabic 20 Jun 94 p 3 TA2106140494 Jerusalem AL-NAHAR Arabic BFN [Text] It has been learned from reliable sources that three Palestinian businessmen, together with Bassam Abu-Sharif, President Yasir Arafat's adviser, are currently studying a joint project for to set up a private television station in the autonomy area. Visitors from Amman say that the four held a meeting last week at Queen 'Aliya Airport and agreed on the broad outlines of their project, including the fact that the project will be managed by Abu-Sharif. They also agreed to hold another meeting soon in order to put the final touches on the project.
